title: Best of The SXSW Playlist, Part 3
description:
Part 3 of 6. Rather pleased at the feedback I&#039;m getting thus far; thanks for the positive comments. I know that a lot of people are going to dislike a lot of the things I have here, because there were 758 songs, and I&#039;m sure everyone could pick out different favourites. However, I like to think that I hit the nail on the head at least every once in a while, and you all end up with something that you didn&#039;t have before, which is the reason that you&#039;re downloading this compressed version of the SXSW Playlist and the reason that I downloaded and listened to the whole thing. Your list:

1.Exodus Honey-Honeycut
2.Crime Does Pay-The Hourly Radio
3.Wine Red-The Hush Sound
4.House Up On The Hill-Ian Moore
5.In This City-Iglu and Hartly
6.Julia, We Don&#039;t Live In The 60&#039;s-The Indelicates
7.Inside and Outside-Intuitive Music Orchestra
8.Out Come The Wolves-Jacob Golden
9.Cheney&#039;s Toy-James McMurty
10.Faster Than Cars Drive-Kate Tucker and The Sons of Sweden
11.Muscle Hair-Kevin Shields
12.10,000 Lakes-Kid Dakota
13.Misadventures of the Campaign Kids-King of Prussia
14.What We Wanted-Krief
15.Restless-Langhorn Slim
16.Robot Ponies-Laura Barrett
17.We Are Gods! We Are Wolves!-Le Loup
18.Nascent Part I-Leslie Keffer
19.Punch Balls-Lexie Mountain Boys
20.Cherry Chapstick-Lil&#039; Cap&#039;n Travis
21.Let&#039;s Get Crazy-Limbeck
22.On My Chest(Remix)-Lissie
23.The World Should Revolve Around Me-Little Jackie
24.Japanese Candy-Little Teeth
25.Coup D&#039;Etat-Lord T and Eloise


A few notes:
-Muscle Hair might sound a tad abrasive to some people
-Intuitive Music Orchestra is awesome
-On My Chest is currently an obsession of mine; I&#039;ve probably listened to it five or six times today already
-Some of these artists have things coming out later this year, and you won&#039;t be able to find anything from them other than this. Lissie is among them(if she&#039;s not, please tell me. Please). So take advantage, and if you find something that you love but can&#039;t find more of, welcome to my nightmare.
